# SQL Session Variable Style

- For SQL templates in this workspace, define parameters as session variables at the top of the file.
- Prefer `SET @name = ...;` before any `SELECT`, `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, or `DELETE`.
- Reuse `@variables` in query bodies instead of repeating inline transforms like `UUID_TO_BIN(:id)`.

## Preferred Pattern

```sql
SET @entityId = UUID_TO_BIN(:entityId);
SET @name = :name;

UPDATE ENTITY
SET NAME = @name
WHERE ID = @entityId
;
```